Map of current zoning structure in Community Board 9 before ‘City of Yes’ zoning proposal

Community Board 9 members are wary that the “City of Yes” zoning proposal will make zoning regulations more flexible and allow for greater overlap of commercial and residential areas. Many worry that this will exacerbate the shortage of residential real estate and affordable housing and cause residential disturbances.

Combined

Commercial and residential overlap currently exists in part of this area.

Commercial

Manufacturing

Residential

Special zoning

Note: Combined zoning refers to the M1-5/R7-2 zoning district which is a combination of manufacturing, commercial, and community facilities.

Source: New York City Department of City Planning

Graphic by Diya Nair
